1
00:00:00,720 --> 00:00:07,350
­Naeil's Cantabile

2
00:00:15,020 --> 00:00:21,040
Sonata for 2 Pianso in D Major, K.448 by Amadeus Moz

3
00:00:25,020 --> 00:00:35,030
Timing and subtitles by the
🔔The Virtuoso🔔 Team @viki.com

4
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:40,550
Bravo! Brava! Nice!

5
00:01:40,550 --> 00:01:43,902
- That was really nice.
- Thank you.

6
00:01:47,281 --> 00:01:49,409
Seol Nae Il?

7
00:01:49,409 --> 00:01:51,035
Orabang...
(Orabang-Jeju version of Oppa)

8
00:01:51,035 --> 00:01:54,838
Nae Il...
Look at me, your Orabang.

9
00:01:54,838 --> 00:01:56,950
Orabang... I can't...

10
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,542
My heart is pounding...

11
00:01:58,542 --> 00:02:00,359
What's wrong?

12
00:02:04,632 --> 00:02:07,127
-Orabang?
-Is she always this weird?

13
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:10,412
Yes. Shouldn't you know that by now?

14
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:13,707
Anyways, what did you think?

15
00:02:13,707 --> 00:02:16,292
Wasn't it fun to just play
for the first time in a while?

16
00:02:16,292 --> 00:02:20,881
Was this a lesson for me
rather than Nae Il?

17
00:02:21,899 --> 00:02:24,926
Listening to your duet I realized...

18
00:02:25,410 --> 00:02:27,055
You...

19
00:02:27,635 --> 00:02:29,606
Want to conduct right?

20
00:02:31,210 --> 00:02:38,000
identify the classical music

21
00:02:45,950 --> 00:02:49,520
­

22
00:02:50,469 --> 00:02:54,332
My goodness, my heart is
tightening and pounding hard.

23
00:02:54,332 --> 00:02:56,875
What's going on?

24
00:02:56,875 --> 00:02:58,820
It's love.

25
00:03:15,529 --> 00:03:20,733
Nae Il, you've fallen
in love with me.

26
00:03:27,583 --> 00:03:31,188
Orabang, I love you!

27
00:03:33,030 --> 00:03:40,060
identify the classical music

28
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:51,340
Change your major.

29
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:53,066
Conducting is not
about conductor's scores.

30
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:55,743
It's about managing people, the musicians.

31
00:03:55,743 --> 00:03:59,613
You can never be a good
conductor by yourself.

32
00:03:59,613 --> 00:04:03,685
Don't you want to conduct in reality,
not just in your head?

33
00:04:49,648 --> 00:04:53,527
Orabang! Nae Il is coming!

34
00:04:53,527 --> 00:04:56,130
Yes, it's love!

35
00:04:56,130 --> 00:04:59,074
Orabang, wait for me!

36
00:05:08,408 --> 00:05:12,537
Orabang? Orabang? Orabang...

37
00:05:18,172 --> 00:05:22,448
Orabang!

38
00:05:22,448 --> 00:05:25,716
You don't even give me time
to agonize for a while.

39
00:05:25,716 --> 00:05:27,669
Orabang!

40
00:05:29,712 --> 00:05:35,368
Orabang, my toes tickled
while I was playing.

41
00:05:35,368 --> 00:05:37,953
My body was shivering...

42
00:05:37,953 --> 00:05:40,664
I was so happy...

43
00:05:44,578 --> 00:05:46,802
But...

44
00:05:46,802 --> 00:05:49,484
But now...

45
00:05:50,434 --> 00:05:55,469
My toes are ticklish because I
want to jump into your arms.

46
00:05:55,469 --> 00:05:58,758
Hold it. You can do that.

47
00:06:01,178 --> 00:06:03,822
I realized what this is.

48
00:06:03,822 --> 00:06:06,748
-What?
-It's love!

49
00:06:06,748 --> 00:06:09,394
Orabang, I'm in love!

50
00:06:09,394 --> 00:06:12,721
-No, it's not love!
-When I think about you,

51
00:06:12,721 --> 00:06:16,877
my heart tightens, hurts and flutters.

52
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:19,062
No!

53
00:06:19,062 --> 00:06:20,297
Hey!

54
00:06:20,297 --> 00:06:25,226
It's just your body reacting to
a rush of adrenaline.

55
00:06:25,226 --> 00:06:28,013
Seol Nae Il, don't get ahead
of yourself and calm down.

56
00:06:28,013 --> 00:06:31,533
It could be a heart disease,
get it checked by a doctor.

57
00:06:31,533 --> 00:06:33,935
Make sure to get
your brain tested, too.

58
00:06:34,478 --> 00:06:37,855
It'll be easier to hug you
and find out. Orabang!

59
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:40,056
Orabang...

60
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:45,030
You're forbidden to come any
closer than this from now on.

61
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:46,957
If not to your chest,
then just your back.

62
00:06:46,957 --> 00:06:49,338
Your back should be fine!

63
00:06:49,338 --> 00:06:51,881
You can't do that either!

64
00:06:54,665 --> 00:06:58,168
Orabang, just once!

65
00:06:58,168 --> 00:07:01,604
Hold me in your arms just once!

66
00:07:01,604 --> 00:07:06,709
- Don't follow me!
- Orabang, Orabang, Orabang!

67
00:07:07,344 --> 00:07:09,946
I got more than I was expecting.

68
00:07:10,514 --> 00:07:13,766
A performance with Cha Yoo Jin...

69
00:07:19,398 --> 00:07:23,927
His long legs helped him
run away fast.

70
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:29,156
Even if he runs away,
it's to my home.

71
00:07:29,156 --> 00:07:31,536
Orabang, Orabang...

72
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:35,921
Thank you! I was dying of thirst.

73
00:07:35,921 --> 00:07:39,445
- So refreshing!
- You are...

74
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,647
A piano major?

75
00:07:44,647 --> 00:07:46,658
How did you know?

76
00:07:46,658 --> 00:07:48,415
I knew it...

77
00:07:49,189 --> 00:07:52,730
I heard piano sounds
from you that attract people.

78
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:56,275
Which music? Mozart? Schubert?
Or Chopin?

79
00:07:56,275 --> 00:08:00,103
None of those... Violin Sonata...

80
00:08:00,103 --> 00:08:02,937
No. 5? by Beethoven.

81
00:08:02,937 --> 00:08:06,324
I don't know that one.
I guess you didn't hear anything from me.

82
00:08:06,324 --> 00:08:08,643
-Wait, wait.
- Wait!

83
00:08:08,643 --> 00:08:11,437
Meeting like this could be destiny...

84
00:08:11,437 --> 00:08:14,577
Do you want to accompany
my performance?

85
00:08:25,930 --> 00:08:29,450
text

86
00:08:30,886 --> 00:08:32,554
What would you like?

87
00:08:32,554 --> 00:08:37,290
-Today... I'll take the mackerel.
-Of course...

88
00:08:37,290 --> 00:08:41,071
you have an eye
for the freshest one.

89
00:08:44,139 --> 00:08:48,820
Orabang, let's have a nice, quiet dinner together,
just the two of us.

90
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:50,698
Sul Raeim?
(Meaning to be excited. Sounds like Sul Nae Il)

91
00:08:51,337 --> 00:08:54,743
Orabang!

92
00:08:54,743 --> 00:08:56,728
This girl, really...

93
00:08:56,728 --> 00:08:59,088
When did she get my number?

94
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:02,075
Don't even dream of it!

95
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:11,593
I'll take one more please.

96
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:22,904
Is it good?

97
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:30,696
- What do I do?
- You have something on you.

98
00:09:30,696 --> 00:09:33,789
- Can I eat this too?
- Of course. You can finish it.

99
00:09:33,789 --> 00:09:35,701
Mix it together.

100
00:09:35,701 --> 00:09:38,044
Here, ah.

101
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:42,707
"Much better...

102
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:47,540
than what my mom

103
00:09:49,150 --> 00:09:51,380
makes?"

104
00:09:55,493 --> 00:09:57,662
Cheers for our performance together!

105
00:09:57,662 --> 00:10:00,948
- Waterloo!
- Beethoven!

106
00:10:00,948 --> 00:10:03,235
Do you want anything else?
Just tell me.

107
00:10:03,235 --> 00:10:05,606
Whatever you desire.

108
00:10:05,606 --> 00:10:09,666
- Of course my father will cook...
- Yes, yes.

109
00:10:09,666 --> 00:10:14,388
Order anything you want to eat,
even if it's not on the menu.

110
00:10:14,388 --> 00:10:18,516
You're my son's partner,
so I'll make you anything!

111
00:10:18,516 --> 00:10:21,330
Now, it's a set course this time.

112
00:10:21,330 --> 00:10:25,490
Pork steak, crab risotto,

113
00:10:25,490 --> 00:10:29,700
pasta and Jeju orange.

114
00:10:35,052 --> 00:10:38,505
Can I wrap these to go
instead of eating here?

115
00:10:40,415 --> 00:10:41,808
Thank you.

116
00:10:41,808 --> 00:10:46,161
- Bye Bye, Lak.
- Bye bye.

117
00:10:46,161 --> 00:10:48,356
Be safe.

118
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:50,766
Did I pick the right one?

119
00:10:50,766 --> 00:10:53,987
She was really great with Yoo Jin.

120
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:56,747
-Didn't you see her hands?
-Her hands?

121
00:10:56,747 --> 00:10:59,421
They're big and long...

122
00:10:59,421 --> 00:11:01,794
those hands are good for playing the piano.

123
00:11:01,794 --> 00:11:03,580
The hands of Seo Ye Jin and
Yim Seul Ho are like that, too.

124
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:06,560
Wow, dad... Sounding professional!

125
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:08,585
You can be a critic now.

126
00:11:08,585 --> 00:11:11,730
I should know enough not
to embarrass my son.

127
00:11:13,298 --> 00:11:16,610
It's my job to support you until

128
00:11:16,610 --> 00:11:20,720
your music fills the Seoul Arts Center.

129
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:25,309
It's getting busy again.
Welcome!

130
00:11:34,695 --> 00:11:38,997
It'll be so good! Orabang...

131
00:11:55,074 --> 00:11:57,471
You follow anyone who feeds you.

132
00:11:57,471 --> 00:11:59,530
Why did you come here anyways?

133
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:05,926
You ate so much,
just go home now!

134
00:12:05,926 --> 00:12:08,093
Sloth, tick...

135
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:12,774
Since when was I a sloth and a tick?

136
00:12:12,774 --> 00:12:16,101
-What's going on?
-Aren't you going to let me in?

137
00:12:16,101 --> 00:12:19,495
Will you keep me stand here?

138
00:12:25,930 --> 00:12:28,056
Come in.

139
00:12:39,343 --> 00:12:41,769
No...

140
00:12:41,791 --> 00:12:45,539
-Why are you here?
-Did I need a reason before?

141
00:12:45,539 --> 00:12:49,047
We were friends before
we started dating.

142
00:12:49,047 --> 00:12:51,088
What's wrong with you?

143
00:12:51,088 --> 00:12:54,691
I might take it as you still
having feelings for me.

144
00:12:54,691 --> 00:12:56,659
You're really...

145
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:01,881
What's the problem?
Is it your music or men?

146
00:13:01,881 --> 00:13:05,284
This is why a friend
of 10 years is great.

147
00:13:07,996 --> 00:13:11,874
You know our next performance is
Carmen. But I'm Micaela.

148
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:14,165
The person who
was always my maid, is Carmen.

149
00:13:14,165 --> 00:13:15,581
I have work to do.

150
00:13:15,581 --> 00:13:18,092
What? Instant ramen?

151
00:13:18,092 --> 00:13:20,717
Yes, Instant ramen.

152
00:13:20,717 --> 00:13:22,969
You shouldn't treat me badly.

153
00:13:22,969 --> 00:13:26,355
-I brought amazing news.
-I'm not interested.

154
00:13:26,355 --> 00:13:28,849
It has something to do
with conducting.

155
00:13:29,685 --> 00:13:34,086
Depending on how you treat me...
I'll release the newsoff-the-record,

156
00:13:34,086 --> 00:13:36,799
so try your best.

157
00:13:48,412 --> 00:13:51,066
I can't hear them!

158
00:13:51,066 --> 00:13:53,266
Now I should be able
to hear them.

159
00:13:54,668 --> 00:13:56,995
I can't hear!

160
00:14:08,557 --> 00:14:11,459
What are you doing?
Get away from him!

161
00:14:32,838 --> 00:14:35,888
They were together all night?

162
00:14:37,461 --> 00:14:39,358
Orabang...

163
00:14:40,714 --> 00:14:43,650
Is this the end for us?

164
00:14:44,301 --> 00:14:45,953
Is it?

165
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,059
Get yourself together!

166
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:56,247
You should earn your keep after
eating my father's food for free!

167
00:15:00,109 --> 00:15:02,107
That's how love is.

168
00:15:02,107 --> 00:15:06,015
It leaves behind nothing.

169
00:15:09,284 --> 00:15:11,919
Did you get dumped?

170
00:15:11,919 --> 00:15:16,249
The only thing left is
an empty heart.

171
00:15:17,382 --> 00:15:18,620
Get yourself together.

172
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:22,630
After the test,
you can fall apart all you want.

173
00:15:24,658 --> 00:15:29,219
Now that I lost my love,
what's the big deal about a test?

174
00:15:29,219 --> 00:15:31,098
Of course it's important!

175
00:15:31,098 --> 00:15:35,912
My test is more important
than your love!

176
00:15:37,319 --> 00:15:39,564
Jeez...

177
00:15:42,991 --> 00:15:45,786
Fine, I'll get the one you
love back for you.

178
00:15:45,786 --> 00:15:47,656
Who dumped you?

179
00:15:47,656 --> 00:15:50,596
My Sunbae.

180
00:15:50,596 --> 00:15:54,600
Your Sunbae? Who in your class...

181
00:15:57,791 --> 00:16:00,618
It can't be Cha Yoo Jin...

182
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:04,012
Is it?

183
00:16:04,012 --> 00:16:07,756
Why does it have to
be that rude prick...

184
00:16:07,756 --> 00:16:09,640
Wow, Seol Nae Il,

185
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:13,080
your type is
more ambitious than you look.

186
00:16:14,558 --> 00:16:18,152
Wait a minute... Cha Yoo Jin...

187
00:16:20,272 --> 00:16:24,376
Is she your rival?
Prima donna Chae Do Kyung?

188
00:16:26,471 --> 00:16:29,774
Is her name Chae Do Kyung?

189
00:16:30,455 --> 00:16:33,482
- Give it to me!
- Hey, let go!

190
00:16:33,482 --> 00:16:35,412
Hey, it can't happen.

191
00:16:35,412 --> 00:16:38,401
You lost.
I can't make this happen.

192
00:16:38,401 --> 00:16:40,150
You said you'd help me, Lak.

193
00:16:40,150 --> 00:16:42,677
Hey, there is a limit to what I can do.
Don't you know Do Kyung?

194
00:16:42,677 --> 00:16:44,745
- I don't know her. Who is she?
- Don't you have a conscience?

195
00:16:44,745 --> 00:16:46,907
What's a conscience?
Is it something I can eat?

196
00:16:46,907 --> 00:16:50,244
Girl... You have to have a little
class for me to push you forward.

197
00:16:50,244 --> 00:16:53,146
What do you mean? I'm better.

198
00:17:10,155 --> 00:17:12,557
Stop it already.

199
00:17:15,827 --> 00:17:18,496
Prima donna in voice major, Miss Han Eum
and the only daughter of Gaon Instruments.

200
00:17:18,496 --> 00:17:20,234
and the only daughter of Gaon Instruments.

201
00:17:20,234 --> 00:17:22,269
Chae Do Kyung?

202
00:17:22,269 --> 00:17:25,721
You know her very well.
Are you interested?

203
00:17:27,696 --> 00:17:30,695
All of the instruments at our school
are from her father's company.

204
00:17:30,695 --> 00:17:32,540
And...

205
00:17:33,090 --> 00:17:35,470
she's pretty.

206
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:38,308
Men...

207
00:17:38,308 --> 00:17:41,846
She's pretty, pretty and pretty.

208
00:17:41,846 --> 00:17:46,549
I heard they broke up,
but I guess they're together again.

209
00:17:46,549 --> 00:17:50,285
Of course, because she's pretty.

210
00:17:50,285 --> 00:17:53,463
-Thank you, please enjoy.
-Bye.

211
00:17:53,463 --> 00:17:55,285
I'll really tell you now.

212
00:17:55,285 --> 00:17:57,686
-Don't you believe me?
-I'm not curious.

213
00:17:57,686 --> 00:18:00,712
Dragging me to re-audition and a trip
to the cafe with that excuse...

214
00:18:00,712 --> 00:18:03,636
It's more than enough that you
dragged me around for two hours.

215
00:18:03,636 --> 00:18:06,104
Franz von Stresemann.

216
00:18:11,758 --> 00:18:16,047
I heard he's coming to our school.
As a professor.

217
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:27,942
You haven't told me your condition.

218
00:18:27,942 --> 00:18:31,570
Let's get it over with.
Why do you keep delaying it?

219
00:18:31,570 --> 00:18:34,121
I'll tell you later.

220
00:18:34,121 --> 00:18:36,517
- But wait...
- I have a class.

221
00:18:36,517 --> 00:18:40,781
Professor Ahn,
are you playing with me?

222
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:48,423
Thank you.

223
00:18:54,613 --> 00:18:56,200
Why did that rude prick come here?

224
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:58,330
-Why is he in such good mood?
-Who?

225
00:18:58,330 --> 00:19:01,356
Who else just walked out
except for that rude prick?

226
00:19:01,356 --> 00:19:05,476
Cha Yoo Jin?
He put in a transfer request.

227
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:09,073
[Transfer Request]

228
00:19:23,205 --> 00:19:24,780
Get yourself together!

229
00:19:24,780 --> 00:19:27,109
The piano is the only thing
you have left now!

230
00:19:27,109 --> 00:19:30,830
You need to play the piano
to prove you have some value!

231
00:19:30,830 --> 00:19:35,473
If I play the piano well,
will he come to see me?

232
00:19:35,473 --> 00:19:39,350
Of course! If you play the piano well,
all your problems will be solved.

233
00:19:39,350 --> 00:19:43,650
Or... if you really need a boyfriend...

234
00:19:44,685 --> 00:19:46,768
I'll date you.

235
00:19:49,631 --> 00:19:51,540
What did you say?

236
00:19:52,484 --> 00:19:56,396
Are you motivated to play
the piano now?

237
00:19:58,108 --> 00:20:01,185
My goodness, Lak... Have I been
looking at my Orabang for too long?

238
00:20:01,185 --> 00:20:04,130
Now I'm looking at you,
Lak, you look like a squid.

239
00:20:04,130 --> 00:20:06,071
- Wrinkly and all...
- Squid?

240
00:20:06,071 --> 00:20:09,293
I want to eat the squid over
rice that my Orabang made for me.

241
00:20:09,293 --> 00:20:12,195
-Cha Yoo Jin made you calamari over rice?
-Yes.

242
00:20:12,195 --> 00:20:15,177
Tuna stir-fried
rice and steak, too.

243
00:20:15,177 --> 00:20:17,034
This is an amazing green light.

244
00:20:17,034 --> 00:20:21,387
Nae Il, so you two
were flirting with each other.

245
00:20:22,095 --> 00:20:23,849
Flirting?

246
00:20:23,849 --> 00:20:26,100
Between my Orabang and I?

247
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:28,519
Guys never buy food for
girls they don't like.

248
00:20:28,519 --> 00:20:30,487
But he even cooked for you?

249
00:20:30,487 --> 00:20:34,782
Nae Il, it's all on you now.

250
00:20:35,469 --> 00:20:39,489
Lak, what should I do?

251
00:20:39,489 --> 00:20:42,162
-Intimacy.
-Intimacy?

252
00:20:42,162 --> 00:20:44,859
For guys, it's the touch.
Always the touch.

253
00:20:44,859 --> 00:20:46,936
Why would Yoo Jin make you 'over rice'

254
00:20:46,936 --> 00:20:48,874
leaving out stews and braised dishes?

255
00:20:48,874 --> 00:20:52,209
-The answer was there!
-And the answer is?

256
00:20:52,209 --> 00:20:54,111
Dive in.

257
00:20:54,111 --> 00:20:57,736
-He's asking to be hugged!
-Hug him?

258
00:20:57,736 --> 00:20:59,367
Hug him! Just go hug him!

259
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:01,051
- Like this?
- Yes, Hug him.

260
00:21:01,051 --> 00:21:03,370
Dive into what?

261
00:21:03,370 --> 00:21:07,709
If you're plotting to commit a crime,
shouldn't you at least close the door?

262
00:21:07,709 --> 00:21:10,372
Orabang, you've come to see me.

263
00:21:10,372 --> 00:21:14,899
-After abandoning Do Kyung...
-Why do you bring up Do Kyung here?

264
00:21:16,777 --> 00:21:20,203
Orabang, I know everything.

265
00:21:20,203 --> 00:21:23,475
- You were together all night...
- Together?

266
00:21:23,475 --> 00:21:25,602
But I'm okay with all of it!

267
00:21:25,602 --> 00:21:28,259
Doing what all night?

268
00:21:28,259 --> 00:21:31,450
♫ ♫

269
00:21:31,450 --> 00:21:35,643
Carmen's Aria 'Habanera'

270
00:21:39,801 --> 00:21:41,728
How long are you going to continue?
It's three in the morning!

271
00:21:41,728 --> 00:21:43,862
Does it matter what time it is?

272
00:21:43,862 --> 00:21:48,197
I'm going to request
a re-audition for Carmen.

273
00:21:51,728 --> 00:21:55,679
-Who'd believe that obvious excuse?
-So that's what happened.

274
00:21:55,679 --> 00:21:57,820
So you practiced all night.

275
00:21:57,820 --> 00:22:00,309
It must have been tough on you.

276
00:22:01,980 --> 00:22:04,131
Stop it already.

277
00:22:04,131 --> 00:22:06,685
I came to see the culprit
of this noise disturbance...

278
00:22:06,685 --> 00:22:09,520
And you have no balance
and no interpretation.

279
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:11,245
Whose fault is that?

280
00:22:11,245 --> 00:22:13,091
I'm about to ruin my test
because of you.

281
00:22:13,091 --> 00:22:14,891
I'm sure it's because of
how you play the violin.

282
00:22:14,891 --> 00:22:17,300
It's not me. The piano is the problem!

283
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:19,480
What did I do?

284
00:22:19,488 --> 00:22:21,306
I wasn't going to say this,

285
00:22:21,306 --> 00:22:24,992
but I got a third place in the junior
national concours.

286
00:22:24,992 --> 00:22:28,170
People around you called you a genius,

287
00:22:28,170 --> 00:22:30,370
so I guess you grew up believing that.

288
00:22:30,375 --> 00:22:32,753
Then shouldn't you pay more attention
to your partner's performance?

289
00:22:32,753 --> 00:22:35,023
You talk like the professors.

290
00:22:35,023 --> 00:22:38,967
Hit the accurate interval, keep up
the beat, follow the technique!

291
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:42,879
Just wait until I graduate.
I'll switch to a electric violin right away.

292
00:22:42,879 --> 00:22:46,498
It'll be the end of
this boring classical music.

293
00:22:48,519 --> 00:22:51,230
It's not that classical music is boring.

294
00:22:51,230 --> 00:22:53,557
It's your lousy performance
that's boring.

295
00:22:53,557 --> 00:22:56,584
What do you know about the violin...

296
00:22:58,278 --> 00:23:00,505
You're going to play it?

297
00:23:01,198 --> 00:23:03,984
Lak, I told you not
to talk back at him.

298
00:23:03,984 --> 00:23:06,241
He's scary.

299
00:23:51,229 --> 00:23:54,169
I know what you're going
to say, so keep quiet.

300
00:23:54,169 --> 00:23:57,321
Rude, arrogant Orabang,
you're so amazing!

301
00:23:57,321 --> 00:24:00,730
-Orabang, Orabang...
-Don't come near me! Don't touch me!

302
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:02,740
Orabang, please give me a hug.

303
00:24:02,740 --> 00:24:06,446
You're such a perfect guy! Orabang...

304
00:24:06,446 --> 00:24:09,615
Orabang, give me a hug!

305
00:24:23,130 --> 00:24:26,140
Go away! This is my performance!

306
00:24:44,015 --> 00:24:46,250
Father really believes that

307
00:24:46,250 --> 00:24:49,530
I'll play at the Seoul Arts Center.

308
00:25:00,109 --> 00:25:02,117
- Yangsu River?
- Yes.

309
00:25:02,117 --> 00:25:05,110
He said he remembered him because
he took him to Yangsu River and back.

310
00:25:07,055 --> 00:25:09,140
Why Yangsu, of all places?

311
00:25:09,140 --> 00:25:11,543
Did he want to feel
the scenery of Korea?

312
00:25:11,543 --> 00:25:14,060
But according to the driver, his

313
00:25:14,060 --> 00:25:17,520
appearance was different from the picture.

314
00:25:17,524 --> 00:25:20,045
How was he different?

315
00:25:20,045 --> 00:25:22,980
Orabang, where are you?

316
00:25:22,980 --> 00:25:24,790
Orabang...

317
00:25:29,847 --> 00:25:32,708
Thank you, my lady.

318
00:25:41,542 --> 00:25:46,052
By any chance... was your father...

319
00:25:49,132 --> 00:25:51,767
a thief?

320
00:25:52,327 --> 00:25:54,580
He stole...

321
00:25:54,580 --> 00:25:59,673
Two stars and
put them in your eyes.

322
00:25:59,673 --> 00:26:03,241
You're right. He sure did that.

323
00:26:03,241 --> 00:26:06,069
Now I see...

324
00:26:07,049 --> 00:26:09,606
you're the thief, miss.

325
00:26:09,606 --> 00:26:13,554
You just stole my heart.

326
00:26:16,044 --> 00:26:17,936
I'm sorry.

327
00:26:17,936 --> 00:26:20,982
Arrest me because I'm a criminal!

328
00:26:22,024 --> 00:26:24,349
If you're sorry...

329
00:26:25,235 --> 00:26:27,832
will you eat with me?

330
00:26:27,832 --> 00:26:29,839
Eat with you?

331
00:26:31,298 --> 00:26:34,203
I don't usually eat with strangers...

332
00:26:34,203 --> 00:26:37,397
I was out of line.

333
00:26:38,707 --> 00:26:40,934
I was adopted when I was little.

334
00:26:40,934 --> 00:26:43,566
But I'm back to Korea...

335
00:26:44,229 --> 00:26:49,266
for the first time
and I eat alone everyday.

336
00:26:50,052 --> 00:26:52,496
I've been so lonely...

337
00:26:58,423 --> 00:27:00,566
Wait!

338
00:27:01,146 --> 00:27:04,216
I have a regular spot nearby...

339
00:27:04,216 --> 00:27:06,559
Would you like to come with me?

340
00:27:14,078 --> 00:27:17,956
Nice timing!
We got here just in time.

341
00:27:18,872 --> 00:27:20,602
The smell is killing me.

342
00:27:20,602 --> 00:27:22,799
This is great.

343
00:27:22,799 --> 00:27:24,805
There is wine, too.

344
00:27:24,805 --> 00:27:27,519
Oh, wine! Okay!

345
00:27:30,300 --> 00:27:33,919
-Garcon, opener.
-Opener, please.

346
00:27:33,919 --> 00:27:36,461
-Garcon? (Server)
-Let's eat together.

347
00:27:36,461 --> 00:27:38,614
It's mine to begin with.

348
00:27:39,941 --> 00:27:44,470
Baby, isn't this a restaurant?

349
00:27:45,097 --> 00:27:48,646
- It's my Orabang's place.
- I don't know you.

350
00:27:48,646 --> 00:27:52,659
-Who are you, mister?
-Orabang, he is...

351
00:27:58,746 --> 00:28:01,073
Who are you?

352
00:28:02,766 --> 00:28:05,379
My name is...

353
00:28:05,379 --> 00:28:07,731
Milch...

354
00:28:07,731 --> 00:28:09,022
[Milk]

355
00:28:09,022 --> 00:28:11,874
-Holstein?
-Oh, Milch?

356
00:28:11,874 --> 00:28:14,470
Yes, Orabang, he is Milch.

357
00:28:14,470 --> 00:28:17,063
Milch Holstein...

358
00:28:17,063 --> 00:28:19,082
Milk cow?

359
00:28:19,783 --> 00:28:23,027
-He knows German...
-I do.

360
00:28:23,027 --> 00:28:25,078
Who are you, mister?

361
00:28:25,539 --> 00:28:27,548
Who are you?

362
00:28:27,548 --> 00:28:30,167
He still has his phone off.

363
00:28:30,167 --> 00:28:32,432
I definitely told him yesterday
that the opening is today.

364
00:28:32,432 --> 00:28:35,032
Why isn't he coming
with a flower bouquet?

365
00:28:35,032 --> 00:28:38,199
Yoo Jin is avoiding you.

366
00:28:38,199 --> 00:28:39,703
- Are you having fun?
- Hey...

367
00:28:39,703 --> 00:28:43,275
Who opens a cafe
in front of her son's school?

368
00:28:43,275 --> 00:28:45,857
He must feel suffocated.

369
00:28:45,857 --> 00:28:47,544
You're obsessed.

370
00:28:47,544 --> 00:28:50,704
What would you know about a mother's feelings
when you haven't given birth to a child?

371
00:28:50,704 --> 00:28:54,618
The mom who nagged about
the fat on her stomach?

372
00:28:54,618 --> 00:28:58,297
This fat around your stomach you got
when you had Yoo Jin...

373
00:28:58,297 --> 00:29:00,724
It's thick. Can't you take care
of it with money?

374
00:29:00,724 --> 00:29:02,689
Leave. Leave after you pay
for your coffee.

375
00:29:02,689 --> 00:29:05,599
If I'm paying, I'm a customer.

376
00:29:05,599 --> 00:29:08,881
How can you tell a customer to leave?

377
00:29:08,881 --> 00:29:11,360
Fine, I won't accept money.
Just leave.

378
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:14,934
No, I'm going to pay.

379
00:29:15,636 --> 00:29:17,980
Treat me like a customer.

380
00:29:25,607 --> 00:29:30,504
Girl, back then and now, you still
have two completely different sides.

381
00:29:30,504 --> 00:29:32,813
Weren't you the same way?

382
00:29:32,813 --> 00:29:35,217
Every time your picture
came up as the chair of

383
00:29:35,217 --> 00:29:38,837
the New York Foundation, I cringe.

384
00:29:38,837 --> 00:29:43,464
-I learned it from you.
-Oh, is that right?

385
00:29:53,318 --> 00:29:56,327
What about the foundation?
Are you done with your life in New York?

386
00:29:56,327 --> 00:29:58,580
How can I stop the family business?

387
00:29:58,580 --> 00:30:00,980
I'll gradually stop.

388
00:30:00,980 --> 00:30:03,851
- What do you plan to do?
- Just worry about yourself.

389
00:30:03,851 --> 00:30:07,445
You're searching for von Stresemann,
but you haven't been able to find him.

390
00:30:07,445 --> 00:30:10,906
You'll have a headache
without von Stresemann.

391
00:30:20,917 --> 00:30:24,213
Do you know this man?

392
00:30:24,213 --> 00:30:27,543
-He's my conducting professor.
-Professor?

393
00:30:27,543 --> 00:30:30,372
No wonder I didn't like you...

394
00:30:30,372 --> 00:30:33,567
You're a student of the
man I hate second most...

395
00:30:33,567 --> 00:30:34,693
What's that?

396
00:30:34,693 --> 00:30:38,378
Baby, the owner doesn't like me,
so let's leave.

397
00:30:38,378 --> 00:30:41,400
I'll treat you to lobster at the finest restaurant

398
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:43,800
in the hotel that I'm staying.

399
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:46,330
- Lobster?
- Hotel?

400
00:30:46,330 --> 00:30:48,190
After we eat,

401
00:30:48,190 --> 00:30:51,600
I'll show you my room.

402
00:30:52,419 --> 00:30:56,065
At night... the night view from my room is great.

403
00:30:56,065 --> 00:31:00,206
-Who'd go to such a place?
-I've never had lobster before.

404
00:31:00,206 --> 00:31:04,816
Nae Il, you shouldn't
follow this suspicious old man.

405
00:31:05,841 --> 00:31:09,469
Orabang, you should see
the world with innocent eyes.

406
00:31:09,469 --> 00:31:12,183
- What?
- It's bad to doubt with no reason.

407
00:31:12,183 --> 00:31:15,192
Why do you live like that?
Really...

408
00:31:15,192 --> 00:31:18,201
- Let's hurry out.
- You're blinded by lobster!

409
00:31:18,201 --> 00:31:21,129
- Wait.
- Why? We have to go.

410
00:31:21,129 --> 00:31:24,643
- Seol Nae Il.
- Orabang, I have to eat lobster. Don't stop me.

411
00:31:24,643 --> 00:31:28,078
I'll let you sleep
at my place tonight.

412
00:31:29,437 --> 00:31:31,510
Orabang...

413
00:31:31,510 --> 00:31:34,486
Orabang, I don't care
if it's on the stairs.

414
00:31:34,486 --> 00:31:36,806
Oh, baby...

415
00:31:36,806 --> 00:31:39,455
I'll let you use my penthouse.

416
00:31:39,455 --> 00:31:42,101
-Penthouse? Oh my god!
-On my bed!

417
00:31:42,101 --> 00:31:44,212
Bed?

418
00:31:45,030 --> 00:31:49,675
Baby, my bed is a waterbed.

419
00:31:50,744 --> 00:31:53,564
Waterbed! Waterbed...

420
00:31:53,564 --> 00:31:56,201
My arm as a pillow is an option!

421
00:31:57,501 --> 00:31:59,291
Your arm as a pillow?

422
00:31:59,291 --> 00:32:01,992
Your arm as a pillow... Orabang!

423
00:32:01,992 --> 00:32:04,162
Orabang!

424
00:32:04,967 --> 00:32:07,008
Orabang!

425
00:32:12,110 --> 00:32:16,572
Young little brat...

426
00:32:25,529 --> 00:32:27,666
Orabang on the right,

427
00:32:27,666 --> 00:32:30,243
me on the left.

428
00:32:30,243 --> 00:32:33,871
- Hurry in here.
- Hurry in where?

429
00:32:33,871 --> 00:32:38,834
Get out now! It wasn't enough
that you brought that old crook here?

430
00:32:38,834 --> 00:32:41,378
I can't leave! You're a liar!

431
00:32:41,378 --> 00:32:43,536
You said you'd let me use
your arm as a pillow!

432
00:32:43,536 --> 00:32:46,658
- And you believed that?
- No! No!

433
00:32:46,658 --> 00:32:48,352
No...

434
00:32:48,352 --> 00:32:50,946
Orabang, Orabang...

435
00:32:50,946 --> 00:32:54,382
I'll drop the option of
the arm pillow then.

436
00:32:55,125 --> 00:32:57,194
Orabang, just this one time...

437
00:32:57,194 --> 00:32:59,187
Get lost!

438
00:33:00,948 --> 00:33:05,018
Orabang! Orabang!

439
00:33:06,065 --> 00:33:08,136
Orabang...

440
00:33:08,136 --> 00:33:12,943
I'm not going to move at all
until you open the door.

441
00:33:13,644 --> 00:33:16,408
Orabang!

442
00:33:16,408 --> 00:33:19,201
[Stresemann - Prague Millennium Orchestra Concert]

443
00:34:01,083 --> 00:34:02,867
What the...

444
00:34:13,918 --> 00:34:15,936
Wake up!

445
00:34:19,168 --> 00:34:21,494
Hey, Seol Nae Il!

446
00:34:23,594 --> 00:34:26,897
Wake up! Aren't you going to wake up?

447
00:34:30,053 --> 00:34:31,388
See?

448
00:34:31,388 --> 00:34:35,382
I knew you'd open up in no time.

449
00:34:37,269 --> 00:34:39,835
You're really annoying.

450
00:34:39,835 --> 00:34:43,108
Is von Stresemann's arrival
still undetermined?

451
00:34:43,108 --> 00:34:47,728
We have to know his arrival date
to prepare a welcoming at the airport.

452
00:34:47,728 --> 00:34:52,556
You probably know, but he's extremely
cautious about media exposure.

453
00:34:52,556 --> 00:34:55,278
You don't need to prepare a welcoming.

454
00:34:55,278 --> 00:35:01,257
Yes, I know there isn't even a
single photograph of him but,

455
00:35:01,257 --> 00:35:05,814
it's also rude not to prepare
anything for his arrival.

456
00:35:05,814 --> 00:35:09,022
Of course, he's a world-famous
conductor after all.

457
00:35:09,610 --> 00:35:11,750
Is there another reason

458
00:35:11,750 --> 00:35:15,440
that you're keeping his arrival date a secret?

459
00:35:19,481 --> 00:35:22,224
Yes, there is.

460
00:35:25,401 --> 00:35:27,429
In truth...

461
00:35:27,429 --> 00:35:32,457
Maestro von Stresemann has already arrived.

462
00:35:56,807 --> 00:35:58,652
Really?

463
00:35:59,743 --> 00:36:01,458
He showed up?

464
00:36:01,458 --> 00:36:05,161
You haven't found him yet?
We don't have time...

465
00:36:06,447 --> 00:36:10,617
Are you sure that Franz
came to this school?

466
00:36:27,530 --> 00:36:29,099
What's this? What is this?

467
00:36:29,099 --> 00:36:31,272
We finally got you, pervert.

468
00:36:31,272 --> 00:36:35,224
I know how to read faces...
I can tell he's a pervert right away.

469
00:36:35,224 --> 00:36:39,099
He's been taking photos of female
students, including Do Kyung.

470
00:36:39,099 --> 00:36:41,825
There must be some misunderstanding...

471
00:36:41,825 --> 00:36:44,110
Let go of me!

472
00:36:44,110 --> 00:36:47,470
You got caught red handed, so
don't dare to try anything!

473
00:36:47,470 --> 00:36:50,667
Even his voice is of a creepy pervert.

474
00:36:50,667 --> 00:36:52,927
Franz!

475
00:36:57,593 --> 00:37:00,137
Please let him go. Let him go.

476
00:37:00,137 --> 00:37:03,442
He is Franz von Stresemann.

477
00:37:04,855 --> 00:37:06,715
Mina...

478
00:37:07,336 --> 00:37:09,294
Franz...

479
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:18,202
Franz, how long has it been?

480
00:37:18,202 --> 00:37:21,199
I saw you briefly at the
concert in Munich...

481
00:37:21,199 --> 00:37:24,215
My, that was already
seven years ago.

482
00:37:25,292 --> 00:37:27,894
Has it already been that long?

483
00:37:28,649 --> 00:37:30,483
Mina...

484
00:37:31,168 --> 00:37:33,769
You haven't changed.

485
00:37:35,043 --> 00:37:39,363
You look as good as ever too...

486
00:37:45,599 --> 00:37:47,000
I'm sorry.

487
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:50,894
Let me apologize one more time,
Maestro von Stresemann.

488
00:37:51,547 --> 00:37:53,630
It's alright.

489
00:37:53,630 --> 00:37:56,739
It was a small misunderstanding,

490
00:37:56,739 --> 00:37:58,920
I'm over it.

491
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:00,927
Thank you.

492
00:38:02,204 --> 00:38:06,007
By the way, what about the pictures...

493
00:38:07,646 --> 00:38:10,882
I have work to do...

494
00:38:17,364 --> 00:38:19,531
Professor Do...

495
00:38:19,531 --> 00:38:23,825
Could you leave us for a moment?

496
00:38:24,501 --> 00:38:26,464
Yes, ma'am.

497
00:38:38,610 --> 00:38:40,487
Mom, Dad...

498
00:38:40,487 --> 00:38:42,281
See? I told you to go
to the doctor first.

499
00:38:42,281 --> 00:38:45,249
No, Lak's test comes first.

500
00:38:45,249 --> 00:38:48,847
If he fails again,
he'll get kicked out of school.

501
00:38:48,847 --> 00:38:52,292
And you still slept outside?
You should take care of yourself!

502
00:38:52,292 --> 00:38:54,870
I thought you'd come out soon.

503
00:38:54,870 --> 00:38:58,789
I felt like the door would open any minute.

504
00:38:59,907 --> 00:39:04,953
Your back is really wide and nice.

505
00:39:04,953 --> 00:39:07,913
Move your face before
I throw you away.

506
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:14,326
No!

507
00:39:16,815 --> 00:39:18,523
Nae Il, are you okay?

508
00:39:18,523 --> 00:39:23,747
As long as I'm with you,
I can get through any hardship!

509
00:39:23,747 --> 00:39:26,699
Should I just throw her away?

510
00:39:28,852 --> 00:39:31,379
Sorry, Yoo Jin.

511
00:39:31,379 --> 00:39:33,783
- Did You get hurt?
- No.

512
00:39:36,293 --> 00:39:39,146
Why did you do that?
You startled me.

513
00:39:39,146 --> 00:39:41,739
As if you saw something
you shouldn't have.

514
00:39:42,341 --> 00:39:44,767
I saw something horrible.

515
00:39:46,537 --> 00:39:48,505
Hey, take this.

516
00:39:51,750 --> 00:39:55,628
Hey, why are you handing
this over to me?

517
00:39:55,628 --> 00:39:59,190
Nae Il, can you move your fingers?

518
00:40:09,041 --> 00:40:12,693
She says she'll get better right
away if someone kisses her.

519
00:40:12,693 --> 00:40:15,482
Don't tell me that,
keep it to yourself.

520
00:40:15,482 --> 00:40:17,926
Seriously, I'm going nuts!

521
00:40:24,455 --> 00:40:27,207
Nae Il, can you take the test?

522
00:40:27,207 --> 00:40:28,892
I can't let her sit in front of the piano like this.

523
00:40:28,892 --> 00:40:32,296
Then what? Do I give up my test?
Do I stay another year?

524
00:40:32,296 --> 00:40:34,989
Part of it is my fault...

525
00:40:34,989 --> 00:40:37,345
so I'll do it instead of Nae Il.

526
00:40:39,214 --> 00:40:42,207
Lak, you won the lotto.

527
00:40:47,014 --> 00:40:49,141
I'm really going crazy here...

528
00:40:49,141 --> 00:40:51,315
Cha Yoo Jin will really
accompany a violin?

529
00:40:51,315 --> 00:40:55,093
That's what I said.
Look, how people are gathering.

530
00:40:56,774 --> 00:41:01,044
This rude prick will accompany
a violin performance?

531
00:41:24,531 --> 00:41:26,283
Professor Do.

532
00:41:34,453 --> 00:41:36,955
What brought you here,
Professor Ahn?

533
00:41:36,955 --> 00:41:39,625
Of course I came to see
my student perform.

534
00:41:39,625 --> 00:41:42,243
But what brought you
here, Professor Do?

535
00:41:51,701 --> 00:41:53,506
Cha Yoo Jin?

536
00:41:53,506 --> 00:41:56,396
He had questions about changing majors.

537
00:41:57,100 --> 00:42:00,920
So he came to check on
Cha Yoo Jin's level.

538
00:42:11,782 --> 00:42:13,330
Ten minute break.

539
00:42:13,330 --> 00:42:16,391
What? Why does it have to
be right before my turn?

540
00:42:16,391 --> 00:42:19,020
I'm already nervous to death.

541
00:42:19,020 --> 00:42:20,941
Control your mind.

542
00:42:20,941 --> 00:42:23,301
Just do what you can.

543
00:42:24,711 --> 00:42:27,163
Where are you going?
We'll start soon.

544
00:42:27,798 --> 00:42:29,783
I'm going to pee!

545
00:42:39,810 --> 00:42:42,310
Where are you going?

546
00:42:42,310 --> 00:42:45,000
You're next.

547
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:47,580
I should take my seat.

548
00:42:53,066 --> 00:42:55,434
You can hear well from here, too.

549
00:42:55,434 --> 00:42:58,896
I'm going to watch and
listen from up close.

550
00:42:58,896 --> 00:43:01,823
For your performance.

551
00:43:02,441 --> 00:43:04,518
Seol Nae Il...

552
00:43:11,992 --> 00:43:16,286
Do what I can?
That's the problem!

553
00:43:16,286 --> 00:43:20,333
Yoo Jin's arrogance is his special power.

554
00:43:24,795 --> 00:43:26,821
Student Yoo Il Lak?

555
00:43:28,400 --> 00:43:30,015
Yes, Professor.

556
00:43:30,015 --> 00:43:32,826
I've heard your performance before.

557
00:43:32,826 --> 00:43:37,322
I remember your performance as full of
emotions rather than techniques...

558
00:43:37,927 --> 00:43:40,814
Can I expect a different
expression today?

559
00:43:40,814 --> 00:43:43,794
Ah yes... thank you.

560
00:43:43,794 --> 00:43:48,331
But... the pianist is Cha Yoo Jin?

561
00:43:49,363 --> 00:43:51,940
Cha Yoo Jin...

562
00:43:51,940 --> 00:43:55,586
If he's playing I guess
he'll steal your limelight

563
00:43:55,586 --> 00:43:57,939
No, this is my test.

564
00:43:57,939 --> 00:44:02,195
Right, the main character of
this test is the violinist.

565
00:44:02,195 --> 00:44:05,298
I'll look forward to your performance.

566
00:44:13,387 --> 00:44:16,783
I'm really immature.

567
00:44:42,388 --> 00:44:45,060
Why is there such a big audience?

568
00:44:46,258 --> 00:44:50,378
Forget about the technique, and
pay attention to the sound of my piano.

569
00:44:50,378 --> 00:44:53,771
-Then you'll be fine.
-Of course.

570
00:45:09,001 --> 00:45:13,122
While Beethoven was in pain
from an ear infection

571
00:45:13,122 --> 00:45:18,289
he wrote the Violin Sonata No. 5 in F major, Op 24.

572
00:45:19,928 --> 00:45:24,516
The title of this song
was given by the people.

573
00:45:25,851 --> 00:45:27,361
'Spring'

574
00:45:27,361 --> 00:45:31,403
It is the brightest and the most
beautiful music in violin sonatas.

575
00:45:31,403 --> 00:45:34,946
It reminds everyone of spring's warmth.

576
00:45:59,556 --> 00:46:02,408
Wait! This is spring!

577
00:46:04,181 --> 00:46:06,996
It's a spring day, but
there is a thunderstorm.

578
00:46:18,570 --> 00:46:22,350
Cha Yoo Jin considers
his own pace more important.

579
00:46:22,350 --> 00:46:24,159
Conductor?

580
00:46:24,159 --> 00:46:28,522
Conducting is not about scores,
it's about people.

581
00:46:28,522 --> 00:46:30,992
You have no chance.

582
00:46:35,571 --> 00:46:38,848
I'll follow you, so listen
to the sound of my piano!

583
00:47:00,471 --> 00:47:02,974
Yoo Jin is conducting.

584
00:47:02,974 --> 00:47:05,640
He's coming when I want him to.

585
00:47:05,640 --> 00:47:09,938
Yoo Jin understands how I feel.

586
00:47:09,938 --> 00:47:12,140
We're doing it together!

587
00:47:20,115 --> 00:47:21,808
What a relief.

588
00:47:21,808 --> 00:47:25,052
My Orabang brought in spring.

589
00:47:54,254 --> 00:47:56,465
It must be nice.

590
00:47:56,465 --> 00:47:58,413
The violin or piano...

591
00:47:58,413 --> 00:48:03,808
You could be the best if you wanted.

592
00:48:03,808 --> 00:48:08,046
Of course. I work hard at it.

593
00:48:08,046 --> 00:48:11,271
I started playing the piano and
violin when I was three.

594
00:48:11,271 --> 00:48:14,399
I threw up blood practicing violin
until I came to college.

595
00:48:14,399 --> 00:48:16,559
Did you try that hard?

596
00:48:16,559 --> 00:48:19,368
I don't care if you pity yourself...

597
00:48:19,368 --> 00:48:21,960
Don't degrade someone else's effort.

598
00:48:22,622 --> 00:48:25,365
Thank you!

599
00:48:25,365 --> 00:48:28,058
I'll recognize you
as my best friend from now on.

600
00:48:28,058 --> 00:48:29,893
- No.
- Don't worry.

601
00:48:29,893 --> 00:48:33,505
- You're more than qualified.
- In Orabang's arms...

602
00:48:33,505 --> 00:48:36,283
- I'll decline.
- No need to decline. You know why?

603
00:48:36,283 --> 00:48:39,970
You stood up for me today.

604
00:48:39,970 --> 00:48:43,931
-Everything's worked out.
- Orabang...

605
00:48:43,931 --> 00:48:47,193
What's with these idiots!

606
00:48:58,389 --> 00:49:00,824
-He's changed.
-Yes.

607
00:49:00,824 --> 00:49:03,001
He's changed a lot, hasn't he?

608
00:49:03,001 --> 00:49:04,996
It was...

609
00:49:05,612 --> 00:49:07,902
a good performance.

610
00:49:11,710 --> 00:49:14,062
Father, Father! Father!

611
00:49:14,062 --> 00:49:16,383
What? What?

612
00:49:16,383 --> 00:49:19,656
This is the best day of my life.

613
00:49:19,656 --> 00:49:21,403
I had my best performance yet.

614
00:49:21,403 --> 00:49:23,826
I'm proud of you, my son!

615
00:49:24,565 --> 00:49:27,038
Father, I'm really going
to play the violin now.

616
00:49:27,038 --> 00:49:28,823
I'm really going to practice hard

617
00:49:28,823 --> 00:49:33,285
and fill the Seoul Arts Center
with my soul.

618
00:49:47,976 --> 00:49:52,212
We already have an orchestra.

619
00:49:52,212 --> 00:49:55,291
I'm talking about a special orchestra.

620
00:49:55,291 --> 00:49:57,460
The one that arouses sensation

621
00:49:57,460 --> 00:50:00,470
and moves people's hearts...

622
00:50:00,989 --> 00:50:02,990
Isn't that

623
00:50:02,990 --> 00:50:06,760
the orchestra that you wish for, Mina?

624
00:50:12,751 --> 00:50:14,715
These are the students I chose.

625
00:50:14,715 --> 00:50:16,938
The members...

626
00:50:18,023 --> 00:50:19,333
Who will take this journey with me.

627
00:50:19,333 --> 00:50:24,249
Are these truly the students
for the orchestra?

628
00:50:33,158 --> 00:50:35,445
Even the pianist?

629
00:50:35,445 --> 00:50:39,508
She is the mascot of the orchestra.

630
00:50:40,487 --> 00:50:44,586
It's my request as the maestro.

631
00:50:45,128 --> 00:50:48,956
I can make your dream
come true, Mina.

632
00:50:50,801 --> 00:50:53,794
How can I help you?

633
00:50:54,721 --> 00:50:57,289
Von Stresemann's orchestra?

634
00:50:57,289 --> 00:51:00,416
He'll recruit other orchestra
members, not us?

635
00:51:00,416 --> 00:51:02,546
Yeah, that's what I heard.

636
00:51:02,546 --> 00:51:05,212
Is that why you gave up
your study abroad?

637
00:51:05,212 --> 00:51:08,880
-How did you find out?
-

638
00:51:08,880 --> 00:51:12,128
-It's Professor Do.
-It's obvious.

639
00:51:13,328 --> 00:51:15,648
He'll send a text message to
the students who are chosen.

640
00:51:15,648 --> 00:51:17,526
I guess you're in for sure.

641
00:51:17,526 --> 00:51:20,986
-You look very relaxed.
-Of course I don't know that.

642
00:51:20,986 --> 00:51:25,342
-By any chance... is our orchestra getting disbanded?
-Nonsense.

643
00:51:25,342 --> 00:51:29,735
-Who's better than us in this school?
-That's right.

644
00:51:29,735 --> 00:51:33,288
We might just
transfer under a new name.

645
00:51:34,178 --> 00:51:37,238
I got a message.

646
00:51:43,362 --> 00:51:46,714
Orabang, Orabang...

647
00:51:50,027 --> 00:51:51,953
What is this?

648
00:51:52,905 --> 00:51:55,499
Congratulations on joining S Orchestra!

649
00:51:55,499 --> 00:51:57,501
Please come to the auditorium.

650
00:51:57,501 --> 00:52:01,536
-How annoying.
-You got in? Why a pianist?

651
00:52:02,773 --> 00:52:04,530
Did my phone break?

652
00:52:04,530 --> 00:52:06,770
What if it did?

653
00:52:06,776 --> 00:52:09,662
Yes, that's right. It's broken.

654
00:52:12,341 --> 00:52:13,760
[Orabang]

655
00:52:14,764 --> 00:52:17,074
I don't need your message!

656
00:52:21,129 --> 00:52:24,773
- Don't keep sending it to me.
- I didn't send it to you!

657
00:52:46,375 --> 00:52:49,225
Orabang, wait for me.

658
00:52:49,225 --> 00:52:51,593
Orabang!

659
00:52:52,506 --> 00:52:55,451
The chairman of the board
requested to have dinner.

660
00:52:55,451 --> 00:52:59,279
He said he'll be here
whenever you are free.

661
00:53:03,507 --> 00:53:06,517
-Take care of it.
-Pardon?

662
00:53:06,517 --> 00:53:10,788
Someone who doesn't listen to Mina or doesn't take care of the documents...

663
00:53:12,322 --> 00:53:14,365
I don't like him.

664
00:53:15,137 --> 00:53:17,773
I shouldn't be that person.

665
00:53:17,773 --> 00:53:19,957
I'll take care of it right away.

666
00:53:24,818 --> 00:53:30,056
Of course I should take care of the
change of major form for Dong Woo's son.

667
00:53:34,256 --> 00:53:36,851
What did you just say?

668
00:53:36,851 --> 00:53:40,128
Did you say, 'Dong Woo's son'?

669
00:53:41,455 --> 00:53:45,144
That Cha Yoo Jin is...

670
00:53:46,264 --> 00:53:48,335
Franz?

671
00:54:00,849 --> 00:54:05,704
Unbelievable. Stresemann told
all of us to gather here? Really?

672
00:54:05,704 --> 00:54:08,770
Hey, Nae Il, pinch my cheek.
Let's see if this is a dream.

673
00:54:08,770 --> 00:54:12,423
Stresemann,
is he really that incredible?

674
00:54:13,086 --> 00:54:15,760
You told me to pinch you.

675
00:54:15,760 --> 00:54:19,152
Of course he's famous.
He's my father's favorite.

676
00:54:19,152 --> 00:54:22,582
-I don't know much.
-Why are you here as a piano major?

677
00:54:22,582 --> 00:54:27,312
I wonder if he called us together
since we're a couple.

678
00:54:27,312 --> 00:54:29,724
- Are you okay?
- Lak, why are you sitting next to me?

679
00:54:29,724 --> 00:54:32,352
- It's annoying.
- What?

680
00:54:32,352 --> 00:54:36,860
I have someone
I want to introduce to you today.

681
00:54:36,860 --> 00:54:40,397
I believe you already know.

682
00:54:40,397 --> 00:54:42,750
He is

683
00:54:42,750 --> 00:54:46,130
Maestro Franz von Stresemann.

684
00:54:46,130 --> 00:54:48,331
Please welcome him.

685
00:54:54,153 --> 00:54:57,405
It's Milch! Hello, Milch!

686
00:55:02,369 --> 00:55:06,246
I know him. He's Milch!

687
00:55:13,464 --> 00:55:15,991
- It's Milch!
- He has such charisma.

688
00:55:15,991 --> 00:55:18,144
But he looks normal in person.

689
00:55:18,144 --> 00:55:21,404
-Does everything have to be cool?
-Art should be cool.

690
00:55:21,404 --> 00:55:24,183
You look country,
so your music sounds country.

691
00:55:24,183 --> 00:55:26,436
What? You look like a pineapple...

692
00:55:26,436 --> 00:55:28,712
Quiet, idiots.

693
00:55:31,815 --> 00:55:34,851
Nice to meet you, everyone.

694
00:55:34,851 --> 00:55:39,170
Our lovely dean has asked me
to conduct our school's orchestra.

695
00:55:39,170 --> 00:55:43,100
Our lovely dean has asked me
to conduct our school's orchestra.

696
00:55:44,260 --> 00:55:47,530
Our lovely dean has asked me
to conduct our school's orchestra.

697
00:55:47,530 --> 00:55:49,808
He speaks Korean really well.

698
00:55:49,808 --> 00:55:53,008
-He was adopted.
-Really?

699
00:55:53,008 --> 00:55:56,930
However... like the saying,

700
00:55:56,930 --> 00:55:59,982
transformative ideas
require new mindsets to thrive.

701
00:55:59,982 --> 00:56:03,760
I plan on creating a special orchestra
with you,

702
00:56:03,760 --> 00:56:07,690
I plan on creating a special orchestra
with you,

703
00:56:07,690 --> 00:56:10,920
not the existing one.

704
00:56:11,493 --> 00:56:14,460
As of this moment,

705
00:56:14,460 --> 00:56:16,920
you are members of S Orchestra.

706
00:56:16,925 --> 00:56:21,446
Yay! S Orchestra!

707
00:56:32,376 --> 00:56:34,378
And...

708
00:56:34,378 --> 00:56:38,139
Also, this has found its way to me.

709
00:56:38,139 --> 00:56:41,120
A transfer request.

710
00:56:41,969 --> 00:56:44,505
Mr. Cha Yoo Jin

711
00:56:45,068 --> 00:56:49,437
requested to change
his major to conducting.

712
00:56:49,437 --> 00:56:52,271
Orabang, no.
Do you have to change your major?

713
00:56:52,271 --> 00:56:56,015
We will lose
our Sunbae-Hubae relationship.

714
00:57:15,100 --> 00:57:25,070
team's credit

715
00:57:29,126 --> 00:57:35,664
I swear to you on my name
Franz von Stresemann.

716
00:57:35,664 --> 00:57:40,318
As long as I'm in charge of the
conducting major in this school

717
00:57:41,587 --> 00:57:43,524
Cha Yoo Jin...

718
00:57:45,841 --> 00:57:49,960
you will never be accepted
as a conducting major.

719
00:57:56,020 --> 00:58:01,340
OST's credit

720
00:58:01,340 --> 00:58:05,190
♫ ♫

721
00:58:05,190 --> 00:58:09,570
♫ ♫

722
00:58:09,570 --> 00:58:14,070
♫ ♫

723
00:58:14,070 --> 00:58:18,840
♫ ♫

724
00:58:18,840 --> 00:58:22,900
♫ ♫

725
00:58:22,900 --> 00:58:27,280
♫ ♫

726
00:58:27,280 --> 00:58:31,530
♫ ♫

727
00:58:31,530 --> 00:58:37,540
♫ ♫

728
00:58:37,540 --> 00:58:41,338
Who is the person conducting
Mahler's music so beautifully?

729
00:58:41,338 --> 00:58:44,133
At least it shouldn't
have been this old hag!

730
00:58:44,133 --> 00:58:46,705
I saw the post for part-time job.

731
00:58:46,705 --> 00:58:49,793
He's a world-famous maestro. Trust him.

732
00:58:49,793 --> 00:58:53,571
Drink up! Up, up, up!

733
00:58:53,571 --> 00:58:56,366
Stop saying nonsense! It's love!

734
00:58:56,366 --> 00:58:58,897
Both of you,
get away from me, idiots!

735
00:58:58,897 --> 00:59:02,964
Is it better for Cha Yoo Jin
to change his major or not?

736
00:59:02,964 --> 00:59:06,733
I want to learn to conduct.

737
00:59:06,733 --> 00:59:09,310
♫ ♫

738
00:59:09,310 --> 00:59:13,380
♫ ♫
